<!doctype html>
<html lang="en-US">
<head>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title>{{options.fontName}}</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta http-equiv="x-ua-compatible" content="ie=edge">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
          integrity="sha384-xOolHFLEh07PJGoPkLv1IbcEPTNtaed2xpHsD9ESMhqIYd0nLMwNLD69Npy4HI+N" crossorigin="anonymous" />

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./strib-icons.css">

    <style>
        .strib-icon {
            transition: color 0.5s ease-out;
        }

        .strib-icon:hover {
            color: #8dc63f;
            cursor: help;
        }

        .strib-icon-svg {
            transition: fill 0.5s ease-out;
            vertical-align: bottom;
        }

        .strib-icon-svg:hover {
            fill: #8dc63f;
            cursor: help;
        }

        .strib-icon-svg:hover {
            --strib-star-top: red;
            --strib-star-bottom: pink;
        }

        .example-icon {
            margin-bottom: 2em;
        }

        .example-large {
            font-size: 3em;
        }

        .example-small {
            font-size: 1.25em;
        }

        .example-icon-name {
            padding-top: 0.5em;
            font-size: 0.85em;
        }

        .example-variables {
            padding-top: 0.5em;
            font-size: 0.5em;
        }

        .example-variables span {
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        pre {
            padding: 1em;
            background-color: #DEDEDE;
        }

        header[role='banner'] {
            margin-bottom: 3em;
        }

        footer[role='contentinfo'] {
            font-size: 0.85em;
            padding: 2em;
            background-color: #DEDEDE;
        }

        main > section {
            margin-bottom: 3em;
        }

        .example-icon-fonts .example-large.strib-logo {
            font-size: 2.25em
        }

        .example-icon-svg .example-large .example-svg-logo {
            width: 3.75em;
        }

        .example-icon-svg .example-small .example-svg-logo {
            display: none;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
<div class="container">
    <header role="banner">
        <h1 class="display-1">Star Tribune icons</h1>

        <p>The Star Tribune icons is a font-icon and SVG set to manage icons used in Star Tribune projects.</p>
    </header>

    <main role="main">
        <section>
            <h1>Webfont</h1>

            <p>These icons can be used as a webfont; the main benefits is a bit easier, though limited, to style with
                CSS, as any styles that apply to text can be applied as well.</p>

            <p>To use the Star Tribune icons as a webfont, include the CSS or SASS.</p>

            <pre><code>&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="//static.startribune.com/assets/libs/strib-icons/{{ pkg.version }}/strib-icons.css" /&gt;</code></pre>

            <p>Then use the base class, <code>strib-icon</code> and then the icon class which is always prefixed with
                <code>strib-</code>, for instance:</p>

            <pre><code>&lt;i class="strib-icon strib-home"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;</code></pre>

            <p>Treat the icon like text. To change it's color, simply use the CSS <code>color</code> property; you can
                change it's size with the <code>font-size</code> property.</p>

            <p>&nbsp;</p>

            <div class="row example-icon-fonts">
                {{#each names}}
                    <div class="col-6 col-md-3 example-icon">
                        <div>
                            <span class="example-large strib-icon {{../options.templateOptions.classPrefix}}{{this}}" role="img"></span>
                            <span class="example-small strib-icon {{../options.templateOptions.classPrefix}}{{this}}" role="img"></span>
                        </div>

                        <div class="example-icon-name">
                            {{this}}
                        </div>
                        {{#with (lookup ../options.templateOptions.meta this)}}
                            {{#if aliases}}
                                <div class="example-variables">
                                    <span>Aliases:</span>
                                    {{#each aliases}}
                                        <code>.strib-{{ this }}</code>{{#unless @last}},{{/unless}}
                                    {{/each}}
                                </div>
                            {{/if}}
                        {{/with}}
                    </div>
                {{/each}}
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>SVG icons</h2>

            <p>Using the Star Tribune icons as SVG icons has many benefits including fuller, though still limited,
                styling as any styles that apply to SVG can apply, and multi-color icons can be used. Note that browser
                support is not as good as a webfont.</p>

            <p>To use, include an SVG with class <code>strib-icon-svg</code>, then reference the ID of the icon in the
                URL, which is the name with the <code>strib-</code>, as well as the JS so that the SVG can be loaded
                across domains easily, for example:</p>

            <pre><code>&lt;script src="//static.startribune.com/assets/libs/strib-icons/{{ pkg.version }}/strib-icons.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;svg class="strib-icon-svg"&gt;
  &lt;use xlink:href="#strib-home"&gt;&lt;/use&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;</code></pre>

            <p>You can style the icons with CSS with some limitations. You can only add styles to the root of the icon,
                not to a specific part. Treat the icon like an image and an SVG. To change it's color, use the SVG CSS
                <code>fill</code> property; you can change it's size with the <code>height</code> or <code>width</code>
                property.</p>

            <p>For icons that have default colors, you can change the colors with <a
                    href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Using_CSS_variables" target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener">CSS variables</a>. For instance, adding a different color to the Star Tribune logo,
                you could do:</p>

            <pre><code>.strib-icon-svg:hover {
  --strib-star-top: red;
  --strib-star-bottom: pink;
}</code></pre>

            <p>There are some icons that require a specific white fill, though these should be drawn. If you need to
                update that fill use the <code>--strib-icon-background</code> variable.</p>

            <p>&nbsp;</p>

            <div class="row example-icon-svg">
                {{#each names}}
                    <div class="col-6 col-md-3 example-icon">
                        <div>
                            <span class="example-large">
                                <svg class="strib-icon-svg example-svg-{{this}}">
                                    <use xlink:href="strib-icons.sprite.svg#strib-{{this}}"></use>
                                </svg>
                            </span>

                            <span class="example-small">
                                <svg class="strib-icon-svg example-svg-{{this}}">
                                    <use xlink:href="strib-icons.sprite.svg#strib-{{this}}"></use>
                                </svg>
                            </span>
                        </div>

                        <div class="example-icon-name">
                            {{this}}
                        </div>

                        {{#with (lookup ../options.templateOptions.meta this)}}
                            {{#if aliases}}
                                <div class="example-variables">
                                    <span>Aliases:</span>
                                    {{#each aliases}}
                                        <code>#strib-{{ this }}</code>{{#unless @last}},{{/unless}}
                                    {{/each}}
                                </div>
                            {{/if}}
                            {{#if variables}}
                                <div class="example-variables">
                                    <span>Variables:</span>
                                    {{#each variables}}
                                        <code>--{{ this }}</code>{{#unless @last}},{{/unless}}
                                    {{/each}}
                                </div>
                            {{/if}}
                        {{/with}}
                    </div>
                {{/each}}
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer role="contentinfo">
        &copy; Star Tribune, Last build: {{buildDate}}
    </footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
